title: When fighter jets get too close
text:
What are these? Beach blast ... Sunbathers ran for their lives as umbrellas and gazebo’s took of as jets flew by. Picture: YouTube/Jukin Media Source: YouTube 
HUNDREDS of holiday makers got the fright of their lives when a plane made a random fly over, causing chaos on this packed beach. 
It’s believed the jets, belonging to a demonstration squadron of the United States Navy called ‘The Blue Angels’ were responsible for the sand blast at Pensacola Beach, Florida. 
The clip shows beachgoers watching one jet practising in the sky, before another low flying plane appears from nowhere. When planes fly too low 
The force of the engines generates enough wind to send umbrellas and beach tents flying high into the sky. 
Some sunbakers can be seen chasing the debrid hurtling through the air, but the majority appear to find the fly-by funny. 
UK’s Metro reports that apparently when ‘The Blue Angels’ aren’t busy choreographing impressive flight routines, pilots like to play jokes on unsuspecting sunbathers. Close call ... Branding on the plane could be easily seen from the beach. Picture: YouTube: Jukin Media Source: YouTube The Fighters 47:03
